<div class="govuk-grid-row">
  <div class="govuk-grid-column-two-thirds-from-desktop">
    <%= register_form_with(
      builder: GOVUKDesignSystemFormBuilder::FormBuilder,
      model: @bulk_add_trainee_upload_form,
      url: bulk_update_add_trainees_uploads_path,
    ) do |f| %>
      <%= f.govuk_error_summary %>

      <h1 class="govuk-heading-l">
        <span class="govuk-caption-xl"><%= organisation_name %></span>
        Review errors for <%= pluralize(upload.total_rows_with_errors, "trainee") %> in the CSV you uploaded
      </h1>

      <p class="govuk-body">
        You cannot add new trainees if thereâ€™s an error in their row in the CSV file.
        You need to fix the errors if you want to add them.
      </p>

      <p class="govuk-body">
        You can use a spreadsheet program to fix the errors in the CSV file.
        Spreadsheet programs sometimes manipulate the data in an imported CSV
        file in way that renders the values invalid. For example, dates can be
        reformatted into dd/mm/yy format.
      </p>
      <p class="govuk-body">
        To prevent this some values in the
        error CSV file that you download are prefixed with an apostrophe, e.g.
        `'2025-06-06`. The apostrophe instructs the spreadsheet program not to
        try to reformat this value. You can safely ignore the leading
        apostrophes. Leave them in place when you fix the errors in the CSV file.
        They are automatically removed when you upload the CSV file again.
      </p>

      <ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number">
        <li>
          <%= govuk_link_to(
            "Download your CSV file with errors indicated",
            bulk_update_add_trainees_upload_path(upload, format: :csv),
          ) %>
        </li>

        <li>
          Fix the errors. If you cannot fix an error,
          you can delete the row and the trainee will not be included.
        </li>

        <li>
          Upload the updated CSV file.
          <%= f.govuk_file_field(:file, label: { hidden: true }, accept: ".csv") %>
        </li>

        <%= f.hidden_field :id, value: upload.id %>
      </ol>

      <%= f.govuk_submit("Upload records") %>
    <% end %>

    <p class="govuk-body">
      <%= register_form_with(
        model: upload,
        url: bulk_update_add_trainees_upload_path(upload),
        method: :delete
      ) do |f| %>
        <%= f.submit "Cancel bulk updates to records", class: "govuk-link app-button--link govuk-body" %>
      <% end %>
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
